\section{Dry mode: [[mk -n]]}

%claude:
Dry mode ([[mk -n]]) prints the recipes that would be executed without
actually running them. It achieves this by skipping [<exec_recipe()>]
and instead faking node completion --- setting each target's timestamp
to the current time and marking it [<Made>]. This way, the traversal
algorithm proceeds as if the recipe had run, allowing [[mk]] to show
the complete sequence of recipes that a real build would execute.

