\section{Strict mode}

%new: not in original mk
%claude:
Strict mode is an [[omk]]-specific extension not present in the original
[[mk]]. It forbids variable redefinition within the [[mkfile]], catching
a common source of bugs where a variable is accidentally set twice.
However, it still allows overriding environment variables (otherwise
recursive [[mk]] invocations would break) --- it only flags variables
that were explicitly set in the [[mkfile]] itself.

<<constant [[Flags.strict_mode]]>>=
